|quote=''੨. ਸ਼ਬਦ. "ਹਉ ਜੀਵਾ ਸਦੁ ਸੁਣੇ." (ਵਾਰ ਕਾਨ ਮਃ ੪) ੩. ਭਿਖ੍ਯਾ ਲਈ ਸੱਦਾ, ਜੋ ਗ੍ਰਿਹਸਥੀ ਦੇ ਦਰ ਤੇ ਫ਼ਕੀਰ ਲੋਕ ਦਿੰਦੇ ਹਨ "ਇਕਿ ਵਣਖੰਡਿ ਬੈਸਹਿ ਜਾਇ ਸਦੁ ਨ ਦੇਵਹੀ." (ਵਾਰ ਮਲਾ ਮਃ ੧) ੪. ਉਪਦੇਸ਼.''
|ref=
}}</ref>
This narration tells Sikh attitude towards physical death of a Gurmukh''.<ref>
{{cite book |last=Dhanoa|first=Surain Singh |date=2005 |title=Raj Karega Khalsa|url= |location= |publisher=Sanbun Publishers |page=97 |isbn= |accessdate= }}</ref> 
It also narrates events of succession of Gur Ram Das over Gur Amar Das.<ref>
{{cite book |last=Siṅgha|first=Sukhadiāla |date=1996|title=Historical analysis of Giani Gian Singh's writings|url= |location= |publisher=UICS |page=3 |isbn= |accessdate= }}</ref>

==Keso Gopal Pundit==
Keso Gopal Pandit (ਕੇਸੋ ਗੋਪਾਲ ਪੰਡਿਤ) is a qualitative name used for a [[Sikh]] in Ramkali Sadu. Here Pundit is not singular but plural. Following is stanza where this name is present:

ਕੇਸੋ ਗੋਪਾਲ ਪੰਡਿਤ ਸਦਿਅਹੁ ਹਰਿ ਹਰਿ ਕਥਾ ਪੜਹਿ ਪੁਰਾਣੁ ਜੀਉ ॥

Traditional commentators thought it to be some historical person during time of [[Guru Amar Dass]].<ref>[http://www.thesikhencyclopedia.com/biographies/hindu-bhagats-and-poets-and-punjabi-officials/kesho-gopal-pandit sikhencyclopedia.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502002721/http://www.thesikhencyclopedia.com/biographies/hindu-bhagats-and-poets-and-punjabi-officials/kesho-gopal-pandit |date=2014-05-02 }}</ref> Linguistically, Keso Gopal Pandit is interpreted as, A Pundit have wisdom of Keso and Gopal are known as Keso Gopal Pundit.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Singh |first1=Sahib|title=Guru Granth Sahib Darpan |format=Exegesis |language=Punjabi |location=India |quote=ਕੇਸੋ ਗੋਪਾਲ (ਅਕਾਲ ਪੁਰਖ) ਦੇ ਪੰਡਿਤਾਂ ਨੂੰ ਸੱਦ ਘੱਲਿਓ, ਜੋ (ਆ ਕੇ) ਅਕਾਲ ਪੁਰਖ ਦੀ ਕਥਾ ਵਾਰਤਾ-ਰੂਪ ਪੁਰਾਣ ਪੜ੍ਹਨ। }}</ref>  In [[Gurmat]], Gurmukhi have knowledge of Keso/Gopal.

